{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:09:05.147Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"text","text":"GOVERNANCE,\n        PermissionGroup.VIEW_ANALYTICS,\n    },\n    UserRole.","accumulated":"I will now outline the Design Plan for implementing the RBAC permission helpers in the backend.\n\n### 1. RBAC and Permission Model Narrative\nThe MVP backend requires a highly secure, clean, and explicit role-based access control (RBAC) architecture.\n- We support three primary roles: `client_admin`, `client_member`, and `gff_admin` (with compatibility fallbacks for legacy `admin` and `client` roles).\n- Eleven discrete Permission Groups represent precise operational boundaries within the GFF AI enterprise platform.\n- Users inherit permissions based on their assigned role. Access controls automatically enforce tenant isolation (users can only access resources belonging to their assigned `client_id` unless they possess GFF admin privileges).\n\n### 2. Metaphor & Data Structure Strategy\nWe will map roles directly to permission groups in a clear, static dictionary configuration (`ROLE_PERMISSIONS`). This provides a single source of truth for all role permissions.\n\n### 3. FastAPI Dependency Strategy\nWe will design and implement the following standard, clean, and explicit FastAPI dependencies:\n- `get_current_user`: (Already existing but will be verified/integrated cleanly).\n- `require_roles(allowed_roles)`: Dynamically enforces that the current authenticated user belongs to one of the specified roles.\n- `require_admin`: Specialized dependency enforcing `gff_admin` (or legacy `admin`) role.\n- `require_client_access`: Extracts `client_id` from the HTTP request path/query params and verifies tenant isolation (i.e., that the user belongs to that client or is a GFF admin).\n- `require_same_client_or_admin`: Enforces that the user belongs to the same client being accessed OR holds GFF admin status.\n- `require_permission(permission_group)`: Enforces that the authenticated user's role has the requested permission.\n\n### 4. Robust Error Handling Strategy\n- Standardized HTTP status codes: `HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED` for unauthenticated/expired tokens, `HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN` for insufficient privileges or tenant cross-talk, and `HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST` for malformed/missing parameters.\n- Highly informative, professional error descriptions that assist integration without leaking sensitive internal details.\n\n### 5. Files to Change\n- `backend/app/core/rbac.py`: Define `UserRole`, `PermissionGroup`, `ROLE_PERMISSIONS`, and existing classes like `RoleChecker`.\n- `backend/app/api/deps.py`: Implement standard FastAPI dependencies and security helpers.\n- `backend/app/test_security_utilities.py`: Expand testing suite to fully validate the RBAC permission system, roles, tenant boundaries, and dependency exceptions.\n\n### 6. Files Not to Touch\n- Any frontend files or folders.\n- Any landing page or GFF AI tools.\n\n---\n\nLet's read `backend/app/core/rbac.py` completely to see how we can modify/replace it. We already read it! Let's write the edits.\nLet's see what imports or standard definitions are needed in `backend/app/core/rbac.py`:\nWe need `Enum`, `List`, `Dict`, `Set` from typing, and `HTTPException`, `status` from fastapi.\nLet's craft the new content of `backend/app/core/rbac.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom typing import List, Set, Dict, Union\nfrom fastapi import HTTPException, status\n\nclass UserRole(str, Enum):\n    CLIENT_ADMIN = \"client_admin\"\n    CLIENT_MEMBER = \"client_member\"\n    GFF_ADMIN = \"gff_admin\"\n    # Legacy fallbacks\n    ADMIN = \"admin\"\n    CLIENT = \"client\"\n    USER = \"user\"\n    DEVELOPER = \"developer\"\n\nclass PermissionGroup(str, Enum):\n    CLIENT_PORTAL_ACCESS = \"client_portal_access\"\n    ADMIN_ACCESS = \"admin_access\"\n    MANAGE_CLIENTS = \"manage_clients\"\n    MANAGE_USERS = \"manage_users\"\n    MANAGE_PROJECTS = \"manage_projects\"\n    MANAGE_AI_OPERATIONS = \"manage_ai_operations\"\n    MANAGE_DOCUMENTS = \"manage_documents\"\n    MANAGE_BILLING = \"manage_billing\"\n    MANAGE_SUPPORT = \"manage_support\"\n    MANAGE_GOVERNANCE = \"manage_governance\"\n    VIEW_ANALYTICS = \"view_analytics\"\n\n# Explicit mapping of roles to their assigned permission groups\nROLE_PERMISSIONS: Dict[Union[UserRole, str], Set[PermissionGroup]] = {\n    UserRole.GFF_ADMIN: {\n        PermissionGroup.CLIENT_PORTAL_ACCESS,\n        PermissionGroup.ADMIN_ACCESS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_CLIENTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_USERS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_PROJECTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_AI_OPERATIONS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_DOCUMENTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_BILLING,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_SUPPORT,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_GOVERNANCE,\n        PermissionGroup.VIEW_ANALYTICS,\n    },\n    UserRole.CLIENT_ADMIN: {\n        PermissionGroup.CLIENT_PORTAL_ACCESS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_USERS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_PROJECTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_AI_OPERATIONS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_DOCUMENTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_BILLING,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_SUPPORT,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_GOVERNANCE,\n        PermissionGroup.VIEW_ANALYTICS,\n    },\n    UserRole.CLIENT_MEMBER: {\n        PermissionGroup.CLIENT_PORTAL_ACCESS,\n        PermissionGroup.VIEW_ANALYTICS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_PROJECTS,  # Let client members see/edit projects & docs as standard platform users\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_DOCUMENTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_SUPPORT,\n    },\n    # Legacy fallbacks mapping\n    UserRole.ADMIN: {\n        PermissionGroup.CLIENT_PORTAL_ACCESS,\n        PermissionGroup.ADMIN_ACCESS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_CLIENTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_USERS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_PROJECTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_AI_OPERATIONS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_DOCUMENTS,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_BILLING,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_SUPPORT,\n        PermissionGroup.MANAGE_GOVERNANCE,\n        PermissionGroup.VIEW_ANALYTICS,\n    },\n    UserRole."}}
